\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Methods:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 A) Correlation-Based Removal\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 # Remove highly correlated features (multicollinearity)\
correlation_matrix = X_train.corr()\
\
# Find pairs with correlation > 0.9\
high_corr_pairs = []\
for i in range(len(correlation_matrix.columns)):\
    for j in range(i+1, len(correlation_matrix.columns)):\
        if abs(correlation_matrix.iloc[i, j]) > 0.9:\
            col1 = correlation_matrix.columns[i]\
            col2 = correlation_matrix.columns[j]\
            high_corr_pairs.append((col1, col2))\
            print(f"\{col1\} <-> \{col2\}: \{correlation_matrix.iloc[i, j]:.3f\}")\
\
# Keep only one from each pair\
X_train = X_train.drop(columns=['totalCharges'])  # Keep 'monthlyCharges' instead\
X_test = X_test.drop(columns=['totalCharges'])\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 Why?
\f1\b0  Highly correlated features add noise, not signal.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 B) Statistical Tests (Chi-square for categorical, ANOVA for numerical)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 from sklearn.feature_selection import chi2, f_classif, SelectKBest\
\
# For numerical features with numerical target\
selector = SelectKBest(score_func=f_classif, k=20)\
X_train_selected = selector.fit_transform(X_train, y_train)\
\
# Get selected feature names\
selected_features = X_train.columns[selector.get_support()]\
print(f"Selected features: \{list(selected_features)\}")\
\
# Remove unselected features\
X_train = X_train[selected_features]\
X_test = X_test[selected_features]\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 C) Recursive Feature Elimination (RFE)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 from sklearn.feature_selection import RFE\
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\
\
# Estimate feature importance using logistic regression\
estimator = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000)\
\
# RFE with k=20 features\
rfe = RFE(estimator=estimator, n_features_to_select=20, step=1)\
X_train_rfe = rfe.fit_transform(X_train, y_train)\
\
# Get selected features\
selected_features = X_train.columns[rfe.support_]\
print(f"Selected features: \{list(selected_features)\}")\
\
X_train = X_train[selected_features]\
X_test = X_test[selected_features]\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa319\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 D) Tree-Based Feature Importance (quick preview of model step)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\
\
