\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Interpret the confusion matrix:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 TP (True Positive): 140 = Model predicted churn, customer actually churned 
\f3 \uc0\u10003 
\f2 \
TN (True Negative): 1050 = Model predicted no churn, customer didn't churn 
\f3 \uc0\u10003 
\f2 \
FP (False Positive): 60 = Model predicted churn, but customer stayed 
\f3 \uc0\u10007 
\f2  (cost: wasted retention offer)\
FN (False Negative): 159 = Model predicted no churn, but customer left 
\f3 \uc0\u10007 
\f2  (cost: lost customer)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Business implications:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 # Calculate business metrics\
TP = cm[1, 1]  # Correctly predicted churners\
FN = cm[1, 0]  # Missed churners\
FP = cm[0, 1]  # False alarms\
TN = cm[0, 0]  # Correctly predicted stayers\
\
print(f"Of actual churners, we caught: \{TP / (TP + FN) * 100:.1f\}%")\
print(f"Of predicted churners, \{TP / (TP + FP) * 100:.1f\}% actually churned")\
print(f"False positives (wasted offers): \{FP\}")\
print(f"False negatives (lost customers): \{FN\}")\
