\f2\fs26 \cf0 # Building a Production-Ready Churn Prediction ML Pipeline:\
## From Data to Deployment in 6 Weeks\
\
**Author:** Ishita Aggarwal | Jul 2026\
\
---\
\
## Introduction\
\
In this post, I'll walk through building a **complete machine learning pipeline** for customer churn prediction\'97from data loading to a live Streamlit app. This was my approach to going beyond tutorial projects and building something that demonstrates real production ML skills.\
\
**Key outcomes:**\
- 86.4% ROC-AUC on test set\
- XGBoost model deployed on Streamlit\
- Full GitHub repo with organized code\
- 5-fold cross-validation + hyperparameter tuning\
- SHAP model interpretation\
\
---\
\
## Project Overview\
\
**Goal:** Predict which telecom customers will churn in the next month.\
\
**Why this project?**\
- Clear business impact (retention = revenue)\
- Rich feature set (21 features, ~7000 samples)\
- Binary classification (classic supervised learning)\
- Deployment-friendly (prediction serves real business need)\
\
---\
\
## Part 1: Data Exploration & EDA\
\
Started with questions:\
1. What does churn look like? (20% base rate)\
2. Which features correlate with churn?\
3. Are there data quality issues?\
\
**Key findings:**\
- **Highly imbalanced:** 20% churn, 80% retention\
- **Tenure is predictive:** Median churn tenure = 12 months, retention = 40 months\
- **Contract type matters:** Month-to-month contracts have 3x higher churn\
- **Price sensitivity:** Higher monthly charges 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f2  higher churn (diminishing return effect)\
\
```python\
